review_blob: Consumed as part of the trifecta. Not a bad malt by any means. Better than Jaguar thats for sure.
Could this be Nattys bastard cousin? I think it just might. Terrible flavor. Average appearance. Not much of a smell.
Pretty bad. More like a seltzer water with food coloring in it. Why do they even make this?

This beer made me question life. I got it as part of a trifecta from the liquor store. We had gotten Melanie products by mistake and the distributor wouldnt take them back. We were getting rid of the Evil Eye because it wasnt selling. Pours a pale straw with hardly any head and any head that existed disappeared pretty quick. Winey with hints of booze. Upon finishing this, I curled up into the fetal position and bawled my eyes out. I wanted to die. Probably wouldnt have this again.
This was bad. Booze, booze, and more booze in the nose. Oh there were also some hints of grass, but they were subdued. Poured the typical AAL color.
This is like ghetto wine. Grapey, with a big hint of alcohol. Left legs on the glass. Really wish there was a 0 rating. This was horrible. Never again.
This was nasty. Left a slick feeling on my tongue that I couldnt shake. Alcohol is very present in the nose and taste. Avoid this at all costs.

My gateway stout. Blackstrap molasses as well as chocolate. Pours nearly jet black with a tan head.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
Very good lager. Deep amber color. Sweet with the honey. Easily drinkable. Can have many and not be impacted too greatly.

Part of the winter pack. Decent coffee stout. If it weren't so hard to find I'd buy it more often.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Not the greatest but not the worst. I've had worse beer. Amber color. long lasting head. smell of cereal grains. Don't let this warm up as it becomes a whole new animal.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
Was pretty good. Nose was hints of grain and corn. I wanted to rate this higher, but for an AAL it should suffice.
Came across this at a hole in the wall liquor store in St. Louis. Booze, booze, and more booze. Appearance is the only thing going for it. Felt slick on the tongue.

Take St. Lucia off my list. Friend brought it back from a cruise to the Caribbean. Similar to almost all of the other Caribbean lagers. Nothing offensive here. Taste was like cardboard smell was of adjuncts.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
Very good Vienna lager. Had in St. Louis from a friend. Malty and toasty. A hidden gem to be sure.
One of the better Mexican beers. This one doesnt have that skunked flavor or smell to it. Came from a "Beers of Mexico" sampler pack.

Skunked, but then again this is a Mexican beer, so it just turns out that way. Couldnt get over the skunkiness and overall this really brought my overall impression of the beer down. I know its in a green bottle, so it wins no points there. Came from a "Beers of Mexico" sampler pack.
This is not an original idea, but it has been honed. Smells a bit like Sprite. This is a Heineken product, and is evident. Slightly skunky,
Bad, but not like its bastard brother Blackberry. Booze is upfront, but you expect it going in. An "ehh" malt liquor.
beer_name: Steel Reserve Alloy Series Spiked Punch 211

review_blob: Holy Christ. Steel Reserve makes wine coolers now? Sickening blackberry aroma that is mixed with cheap booze. I nearly got sick off of this "beer." Booze was up front and in a way that it reminded me of the stinking drunks back home in Hyannis. Im sure if you tossed them one of these they would owe you a "life debt." Sipping this also reminded me of that one guy, you know the one the one who always says that you should definitely try this, but going in you know that it would really suck. This and that strawberry margarita are the two worst things to pass my lips. There should be a Geneva Convention regarding bad beer. Monuments will be erected in memory of those who have suffered drinking bad beers. The monuments shall be inscribed "NEVER AGAIN."
beer_name: Steel Reserve Alloy Series Blk Berry 211

review_blob:
One of the better cheap beers I have had. Taste is sweet corn with a slight metallic twinge. We cannot get this in New England. Had while on a working vacation in Saint Louis. Not the best but certainly not the worst I have had. El cheapo cerveza that gets the job done and gets it done if consumed in mass quantities. The corn goes away if cold enough.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

What in gods name is this? It's a taste so indescribably bad that I cannot place it. Sure it's strawberry, they said. It has 8% abv they said. Mix it with ice, they said. The taste is like a sugary kids cereal that is so cloying that it sticks to your tongue and roof of your mouth. The aroma is booze and you certainly get a nose full of it. The color of the "beer" is like someone played a cruel joke with red food coloring and Kotex. This will never pass through my lips again. I just needed to review it. 25 Oz. can bought at Schnucks Market in Saint Peters, Missouri.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Cinnamon is very subdued. Apples shine through but that might not be a good thing. Was cheap at 2.49. Perhaps the price is a telltale sign. Color is like Bud Light. Booze is also present. It will warm you up if you drink enough.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Water makes a better drink. Incredibly weak beer that left me wanting more. Could drink this all day and not get hammered.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Can. Drank this while visiting my dad in Gouverneur NY. Like a seltzer water with alcohol in it. Could drink these all day long. Cheaper than Bud Light.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Can. Consumed on a hot Saint Louis afternoon in April 2012. Taste was slight. Very smooth. Easy drinking and cheap too.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Not good. Was watery and generally water like. Left me wanting more. El cheapo cerveza. Seems to only be in 40 oz bottles where I'm from.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

El cheapo. Decent but not the greatest cheap beer ever. If I find it, I'll let you know.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Wow. Hangover city right here. I had three of these and didn't get drunk but I got a wicked headache. They must mistreat their yeast. Then again this is hobo juice.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Cheap beer for when you're broke as hell. It was like a freshly mown lawn. Watery too. Probably won't have it again.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

An exceptional beer. Had this New Years Eve 2009. From what I remember it was fruity. There was sediment in the bottom of the bottle that went into my glass.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Bought in Falmouth Mass at Kappy's. Very good porter. Surprisingly since it comes from Nastygansett. Found only during wintertime it seems. Was sweet and delicious.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Had at Warren's Lobster House in Kittery Maine. No head to speak of and there was something off about this beer. It almost tastes similar to PBR. Went surprisingly well with fried seafood.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Excellent porter. Forget what I said about other Baltika products being so so. This and No.9 are the exceptions. Smelled of fruit and chocolate. The boozy undertones were subdued in this beer. One of my favorites to enjoy during the winter months.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

This beer was not good at all. It had a funky metallic taste to it and it seemed like it had expired.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Not that good of a beer. I've had better beers from Mexico (not that many to choose from) perhaps I'm a little too hard on this beer, but it needs to be said. This beer is like Budweiser, little flavor and little attraction. This beer should be sent to the depths of beer Hades.

Was pretty underwhelming for a Mexican lager but then again most of them are. Perhaps I got a bad bottle. Purchased from Friar Tuck Beverage as part of a "create your own six pack" set.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
This was a strange brew for me. Noted hints of treacle and a strange vanilla-esque flavor to it.
This was pretty bad. Was kind of funky in the taste department, and Im sure if I had it at the brewery, it would taste a lot better.
Not a bad cider at all. Quite refreshing. Very little alcohol was present when I took a whiff.

Very good stout. I had this @ old mill stream inn in St. Charles, MO taste was complex and satisfying. Not cloying and overall a great beer.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
I really enjoyed this beer. The apple was different, and not in a bad way. The beer was rather quenching, and pretty inoffensive. On my list to have again, when it comes around.

This is a very delicious holiday ale. Drink this at Room temp, for if you do not, then you will get a cough syrup taste to it. At room temperature, the beer has an extreme bakeshop smell, as though you were buying Christmas Cookies. The taste is spicy, and I detected cloves and citrus.

Worse than Evil Eye. Worse than fermented fruit. This will have you on your ass and let me tell you this: Beware of Black Ice. Now, the buzz can be softened by water and food. I did not enjoy this one single bit.
beer_name: Camo Black Ice High Gravity Lager

review_blob: Tasted and smelled like ass. The appearance was average, simply due to the fact that its a malt liquor. Yes I know not all MLs are created equal. It left my palate in a sticky, cloying, and sick state. Drank for the can.
beer_name: Camo Silver Ice High Gravity Lager

review_blob: Looks like a malt liquor should. Tastes like one too. Smells of that corn chip funk and tastes kid of like ass.
Enjoying as I type. The aroma: like a water treatment facility during a water scare. The flavor: champagne like and yeasty. On the palate: rough. Tobe enjoyed with pretzels.
I like it, although the draught can version is a bit too watery for me. People look at me as if Im crazy for liking the darker beers.

I had this while in Haiti. The bottle is a funny shaped, "stubby" bottle. The beer is pretty nasty. I smelled sulfur, and other related smells. Wont be consuming this ever again. Bottle is in the collection.
Some chocolate is in there, and even some sugar, of all things. I wouldnt drink this again. Simply because I didnt like it that much. The bottle has made a nice addition to my collection.
